                  <msContents>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                     <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item1">
                        <locus>(fol. 1)</locus>
                        <author key="person_66806872">Augustine</author>
                        <title key="work_818">Sermones de uerbis domini et apostoli</title>
                        <rubric>Omelie beati Augustini de Verbis Domini &amp; apostoli </rubric>
                        <incipit>Evangelium audiuimus &amp; in eo Dominum</incipit>
                        <note>Eighty-nine in number: the title is added.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item1a">
                        <note>On five preceding leaves are a list of the sermons, and two sermons. (De non jurando by Augustine, and De Carne, Mundo et Diabolo, beg. 'Adiuua me Domine, ... Corpus fugere': Migne's <title>Patrol. Lat.</title> 38. 962 and [?]): the latter sermon is imperfect, fol. vi being mutilated.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item2">
                        <locus>(fol. 109v)</locus>
                        <author key="person_7386286">Ps.-Augustine</author>
                        <title key="work_3906">Sermones ad fratres in eremo</title>
                        <rubric>Sermones Augustini episcopi morales ad Fratres in heremo</rubric>
                        <note type="annotation">Twenty-five sermons (with notes), a list of which is on fol. 130v.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem class="#tabulae" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item2a">
                        <note>Fols. 131–143r are occupied with indexes of subjects to the two preceding articles.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="3" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item3">
                        <locus>(fol. 143v)</locus>
                        <author key="person_3268904">Paulinus of Aquileia</author>
                        <title key="work_3459">De salutaribus documentis</title>
                        <rubric>Epistola Augustini ad Julianum comitem</rubric>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem class="#tabulae" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item3a">
                        <note>Followed at fol. 154 by an index of subjects.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="4" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item4">
                        <locus>(fols. 155, 156, 159, 179, 180v, 181v, 182, 182v, 244)</locus>
                        <author key="person_66806872">Augustine</author>
                        <title key="work_820">Sermons</title>
                        <note>Nine separate sermons by or attributed to st. Augustine (Migne's <title>Patrol. Lat.</title> 39. 1946, [?], 39. 1783, 39. 2206, 39. 2301, 39. 2303, 39. 2307, 39. 2237, 39. 2264): the one without a reference in Migne beg. 'Quemadmodum desiderat ceruus ... O fons vite'.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="5" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item5">
                        <locus>(fol. 157v)</locus>
                        <author key="person_290254327">Patrick of Dublin</author>
                        <title key="work_3450">De tribus habitaculis animae</title>
                        <rubric>Augustinus de gaudio electorum et de supplicio damnatorum</rubric>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem class="#theologica" n="6" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item6">
                        <locus>(fol. 161)</locus>
                        <title key="work_13982">Prick of Conscience</title>
                        <note>(Latin translation)</note>
                        <rubric>Liber nuncupatus Stimulus consciencie</rubric>
                        <incipit type="prologue">Ab eterno et ante tempora</incipit>
                        <note>In seven books, with lists of chapters.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item6a">
                        <note> At fol. 182 is 'Seneca de Ebrietate', an extract from one of <persName key="person_90637919" role="aut">Seneca</persName>'s letters, and at fol. 244v 'De collacione huius vite transitorie ad vitam eternam', beg 'Eripe me de inimicis ... Sic viuere debemus'.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <note>For items 7–10 (fols. 185–232) see part B.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="11" xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item11">
                        <locus>(fol. 233)</locus>
                        <author key="person_95147024">Jerome</author>
                        <title key="work_2426">Letters</title>
                        <note>(extracts)</note>
                        <rubric>Notabilia extracta de epistolis sancti Jeronimi <note type="editorial">[added title]</note></rubric>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_159-part1-item11a">
                        <locus>(fol. 241)</locus>
                        <note>An extract from Jerome's Rescriptio de cessatione legalium</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
